# Frontend Rules — CareerOS Campus AI

## Next.js 14 app router

- App router only (`apps/web/app/`). No pages router, ever.
- Default to server components. Add `"use client"` only for hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers.
- Route groups: `(student)/` for student surface (active), `(officer)/` for officer surface (Week 4).
- Co-locate route-specific components in the route folder. Promote to `apps/web/components/` only when
  the component is used in 2 or more routes.

## TypeScript

- `strict: true`. No `any`. Unknown types → `unknown`, then narrow.
- All pane-level types in `apps/web/components/panes/types.ts`.
- Cross-service domain types consumed from `packages/ts-types/` once schemas ship.

## State management

- Central hook: `useCareerOSWorkspace` in `apps/web/hooks/useCareerOSWorkspace.ts`.
- Split into `useStudentWorkspace` / `useOfficerWorkspace` when officer surface lands.
- `localStorage` for auth token only. Everything else is server-derived.
- No Redux, Zustand, or Jotai until an ADR approves it.
- No `useEffect` for derived state — compute in render or `useMemo`.
- No data fetching inside `useEffect` when data is route-stable — use server components.

## API calls

- All HTTP via `apps/web/lib/api.ts`. Never `fetch()` inline from components.
- Auth header attached centrally in `api.ts`. Components receive `token` and pass it.
- New endpoints get typed wrapper functions added to `api.ts`.

## Styling

- Dark-theme CSS variables in `apps/web/app/globals.css`. Extend, do not replace.
- Inline `style={{...}}` tolerated for one-off tweaks on existing components.
- New reusable components use CSS classes.
- No Tailwind, no CSS-in-JS, no styled-components — needs an ADR to introduce.

## Components

- UI primitives first: `CardSection`, `FormField`, `MetricTile` in `apps/web/components/ui/primitives.tsx`.
- Pane components: `apps/web/components/panes/`.
- Section cards: `apps/web/components/panes/sections/`.
- Props are explicit — no `...rest` spreads unless wrapping a DOM element.

## Accessibility

- Buttons: `type="button"` (non-submit) or `type="submit"` (inside forms). No typeless buttons.
- Form fields: use `FormField` wrapper with a real `<label>`.
- No `tabIndex="-1"` on interactive controls.
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` without a sanitiser.

## Import order

External packages → workspace packages → relative imports.
No barrel `index.ts` re-exports unless they remove real import ceremony.
